article.headline: Nevada 77, New Mexico St. 67
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- Luke Babbitt led Nevada with 26 points and 11 rebounds and the Wolf Pack defeated New Mexico State 77-67 Monday night. Nevada (9-6, 1-1 Western Athletic) never trailed, shot 52.5 percent and led by as many as 17. Five players scored in double figures for the Aggies (8-7, 1-1), led by Wendell McKines, who had 16 points. Brandon Fields added 13 points and Dario Hunt 12 for Nevada, which outrebounded New Mexico State 38-29 and hit 9-of-20 3-pointers. The Wolf Pack led by seven at halftime and later used a 19-8 run to push its lead to 64-49 with 6:02 to play. Babbitt was 3 of 3 from beyond the arc and scored 15 points in the first half.
